description: For sale: $250,000. Nearly 3/4-acre secluded and picturesque wooded setting in the heart of vibrant St. Paul.  This tranquil setting offers a new owner many opportunities.  Create an abundant garden in which to grow your own produce.  Chef inspired modern kitchen w/duel fuel range and ample storage featuring comfort pull out shelving.  Relax in the inviting Knotty Pine paneled living room featuring cozy wood burning stove. Admire the beauty of changing seasons and abundant wildlife, viewed through a bank of French windows.  Enjoy the feeling of being "up north at a cabin" with the warm wood tones and maple flooring.  Freshly painted generously sized bedrooms. One offering new carpeting w/access to an unfinished attic space for potential expansion. Second w/bird's eye maple flooring and access to a potential roof top porch. Many add'l updates. Conveniently located for work, education, entertainment, dining and boutique shops. Minutes from Mississippi River Rec. Area and Metro Bike Trail.  A SPEICAL MESSAGE FROM THE SELLER:"Having a home in the middle of the city with a beautiful expansive yard that I would garden, watch birds and wildlife, plus relax with privacy, was a gift. As an artist, I would paint in the bright sunlit room that overlooked a tranquil and peaceful vista. Detached from the bustling city in my serene and secluded home, yet just minutes away from work, I enjoyed country living with the convenient commuting, great shopping, unique restaurants, fun events, concerts and festivals that Saint Paul has to offer. Best of both worlds!"

description:
Recently sold: $292,500. Available now!! Fresh and clean Payne-Phalen 2 bed 1 bath duplex w/ Laundry - Available now!! Another great listing from Steve S and Housing Hub! Come and see today!! The finishing touches have been completed on this 2 bedroom 1 bathroom lower level duplex. The unit has fresh carpet throughout except in the kitchen and the bathroom which is tiled. The bedrooms are large with nice size closets as well. The kitchen is large enough to have a dining room table. Downstairs there are 4 brand new washers and dryers that are shared between the 2 units!! You also have a front and back entrance with an off street parking spot behind the building. There is a decorative fireplace in one of the bedrooms with the charm of old St Paul throughout...do not miss this one! Just north of downtown St Paul, this unit is off Payne Ave in a neighborhood that has great eats. Payne-Phalen is a paradise of diverse food options, packed with mom-and-pop soul. From taquerias to Thai, red sauce Italian, there is something for everyone along inside this under-sung neighborhood. Close to 35W and I94 to get you everywhere quickly. This building is pet friendly, however there are breed restrictions and pet fees and deposits will apply.
Tenants are responsible for gas and electricity and trash ($45 monthly) Owner pays for water and takes care of the lawn and snow. This is a professionally managed home from the folks at Housing Hub. Online access makes applying, paying rent and scheduling maintenance a breeze. Housing Hub wants to provide you with a great living experience! $45 per adult. Call or text Steve S. This property will accept a minimum lease term of 12 months. **There is absolutely no smoking in this building.** Here is our application selection criteria for your review:
1. Preferred credit score of 650 or above 2. Good rental history - No evictions, UDs or judgments
3. Clean criminal history - No felonies
4. Income should be 2.5 times the rent verified by pay stubs All information deemed reliable but not guaranteed. (RLNE5526968)

description: Recently sold: $270,000. This handsome 2 1/2 story American Foursquare sits on a double, corner lot and is on the market for the first time in 45 years. Lovingly maintained over the years, the home features natural, quarter-sawn oak woodwork on the main level. A splendid oak staircase in the reception hall, box columns and built-in dining room buffet with leaded-glass doors add to the grandness of the first-floor public areas. The four-season room off the large living area is perfect for an office or enjoying the double city lot view. The first floor also features a large eat-in kitchen and walk-in pantry. On the second and third levels you will find five bedrooms, a sitting area, full bath and 1/2 bath. The back porch features an over-sized screened-in area to enjoy the summer nights. The large garage has a separate space above that could be used as a kid's playhouse/. Updated mechanicals include a high-efficiency water hater and boiler system.

description:
Recently sold: $242,121. I will no longer be setting up showings as of 2/21/16. If you are interested in submitting an application, please do so by Tuesday 2/23/16. Thank you for your interest!!

Lovely 4 bedroom, 1.5 bathroom home with TONS of sunlight. This gem sits on a double lot with flowers blooming from spring apple blossoms and tulips and continues until the last rose fades under the winter snow. Beautiful and well maintained the house features large rooms, an open layout, two fire places, a great storage area, a beautiful sunroom & hardwood floors through out the house. Open to 1-2 VERY well mannered dogs- no puppies please! No cats due to allergies!
********** THis is NOT a section 8 Property************

Neighborhood Description
Great neighborhood with excellent neighbors. Neighbors have block parties and bon fires. Neighbors have a facebook page to keep up to date with neighborhood happenings, resources and more. Neighborhood is close to everything! 15 minutes or less to downtown Saint Paul, 2 YMCAs, University of MN St Paul Campus, hospitals, Maplewood and Rosedale Malls, Woodbury, Mall of America and more. Neighborhood features Phalen Lake and parks. Our house is a half mile jog to the lake and golf course. 

What I love about the home
I love the indoor and outdoor spaces. The patio is great for entertaining and is surrounded by beautiful plants- lilacs, hydrangeas, roses and more. This house comfortably homes any type of family. Its accommodating for a bigger family, but cozy enough for a couple. Lots of windows let in lots of light and fresh air. Security system ready to set up. Front loading washer and dryer. description: Recently sold: $190,000. Great, East Phalen cape cod style with 3BR. New paint throughout. New kitchen floor. Refinished hardwood floors in LR. New carpet in BRs. Bathroom tub refinished. New carpet/paint in partially finished basement. Low-maintenance siding, updated electric, furnace, water heater. Charming home with cove ceilings, picture window in LR, newer windows throughout. Short walk, bike, drive to parks, shopping.

Recently sold: $230,000. Updated with modern and fresh finishes and located next to a park, this adorable Saint Paul home has so much to offer. Featuring a beautifully updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances, granite countertops and sleek and modern cabinetry and tons of storage. The light filled living room boasts original hardwood floors and large windows. The stunning staircase leads to the upper level featuring a loft area, office and 2 bedrooms. The lower level boasts a large family room, beautiful new 3/4 bathroom, laundry room and it walks out to the backyard. The lush, large yard is filled with perennial gardens, surrounded by trees and backs up to a park-very private and offers tons of outdoor space to enjoy. Grill, relax and entertain on the large deck and patio.
